The paper deals with object detection, which is a core problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves training an end-to-end model that fuses semantic attribute prediction with visual features, which suggests the use of machine learning techniques (cs.AI) and deep learning models (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the limitations of state-of-the-art detection methods and the need to incorporate semantic information, which suggests a focus on natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the experiments involve testing the method on image datasets, which suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM).
